priorities were cast
aside to get enough Democratic
votes on board.

01:14.407 --> 01:16.376 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Lisa Desjardins reports.

01:16.409 --> 01:21.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The massive
trillion-dollar-plus
spending deal keeps government
funded through

01:21.514 --> 01:25.218 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the fall and gives this Congress
its first
bipartisan success.

01:25.251 --> 01:27.020 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:27.053 --> 01:28.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: These
are important priorities for
Congress and

01:28.188 --> 01:29.622 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the president.

01:29.656 --> 01:31.558 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
