health office
and to fight opioid addiction.

02:56.009 --> 03:01.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also in the billion, $2 billion
to extend,
permanently, health benefits for
a large group

03:01.247 --> 03:03.583 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of coal miners and their
families.

03:03.616 --> 03:08.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House Speaker Paul Ryan said the
bill makes
America -- quote -- "stronger
and safer."

03:08.188 --> 03:12.325 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But contrast that with
Republican Jim Jordan
of Ohio of the conservative
Freedom Caucus.

03:12.358 --> 03:14.127 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:14.160 --> 03:15.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JIM JORDAN (R), Ohio: I think
you're going
to see a lot of conservatives be
against this

03:15.628 --> 03:17.697 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
plan this week.

03:17.730 --> 03:23.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Why did we last fall do a
short-term spending
bill, if we weren't going to
fight for the

03:23.403 --> 03:25.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things we told voters we were
going to fight
for?

03:25.305 --> 03:29.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: White House
spokesman Sean
Spicer acknowledged Republicans
needed Democratic

03:29.442 --> 03:31.177 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
votes.

03:31.211 --> 03:32.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
This is something that required
60 votes in

03:32.178 --> 03:33.947 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Senate.

03:33.980 --> 03:36.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We couldn't have our entire way
on this, but
we're five months away from
having a 2018

03:36.749 --> 03:41.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
budget, and I think the
president's priorities
will be reflected much more in
that.

03:41.588 --> 03:45.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: With the latest
stopgap funding
measure set to expire Friday,
the legislation

03:45.992 --> 03:49.429 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
