of issues
that were important to
Democrats, as we said,

04:31.871 --> 04:33.606 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Puerto Rico.

04:33.640 --> 04:37.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there is a whole other range
of them,
including, for example, the
National Endowment

04:37.210 --> 04:40.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the Arts, which got a slight
increase
in this as well.

04:40.513 --> 04:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In the past,
we have had
shutdowns, or we came very,
very, very close

04:44.450 --> 04:46.486 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to having a shutdown.

04:46.519 --> 04:48.254 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This wasn't the case in this.

04:48.288 --> 04:52.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The GOP seemed to think that
they were just
going to get blamed if the
government shut

04:52.191 --> 04:54.394 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
down, and that is why they
seemed to have
backed off a little bit?

04:54.427 --> 04:57.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I think that is
exactly right,
because there were Republicans
talking to

04:57.664 --> 05:02.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us privately last week trying to
get reporters
in the framework of, oh,
Democrats will be

05:02.101 --> 05:04.437 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
blamed if this shutdown happens.

05:04.470 --> 05:07.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the very fact that they were
bringing
that up, William, you knew that
they were

05:07.340 --> 05:09.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
worried that they would catch
the blame.

05:09.108 --> 05:11.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Part of that is because they
were blamed the
last time that happened, because
they shut

05:11.944 --> 05:15.782 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
down government over the
Affordable Care Act
and trying to end that.

05:15.815 --> 05:20.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think there's also an
issue with Republicans
that they are concerned that
some of the issues

05:20.186 --> 05:24.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
