three levers
of government, getting stuff
done isn't as

38:04.115 --> 38:06.217 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
easy as they thought it was.

38:06.250 --> 38:09.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president himself has said,
boy, this
is a little bit harder doing
this governing

38:09.587 --> 38:11.422 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thing that I thought.

38:11.455 --> 38:16.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he is rightly pointing to
the fact that
Republicans have never had to
govern before.

38:16.694 --> 38:19.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have been -- most of them
have been in
the minority.

38:19.530 --> 38:22.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have never been with a
Republican president.

38:22.500 --> 38:24.635 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have never had control of
government.

38:24.669 --> 38:26.971 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, this is a brand-new
experience for them.

38:27.004 --> 38:31.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All the old fights that, by the
way, to Tam's
point, have been brewing for
years and years

38:31.275 --> 38:33.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and years -- this isn't Donald
Trump's fault.

38:33.444 --> 38:37.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The divisions between
Republicans on a whole
host of issues have been there,
I would argue,

38:37.882 --> 38:41.419 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going all the way back to the
Bush administration
on a lot of these issues.

38:41.452 --> 38:44.322 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
